verse.lines:
{lang-eng}He fills the throne—the throne above;
Its rights to Him belong;
The object of His Father’s love,
Theme of the ransomed’s song.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Though high yet He accepts the praise
His people offer here;
The faintest, feeblest note they raise
Will reach the Savior’s ear.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}To Him whom men despise and slight,
To Him be glory giv’n;
The crown is His, and His by right
The highest place in heav’n.{/lang-eng}
